txt.en: 'Attack them!'
You successfully disable the alarm, but your cover has been blown!
'Hmmph...'
'You there! What are you doing here?'
'Let me see your orders!'
'Let's see how you handle my poisoned blades!'
'This is a restricted area!'
'What are you idiots doing still standing there? I thought I told you to get back to work!'
The Orc looks in your direction...
'Huh? Who's been messing with this?'
'You have arrived at the perfect time!'
'The alarm doesn't work!'
'You have the honour of witnessing the power of my warriors before Lothlórien!'
'No alarm? I'll have to handle this myself!'
'Hey, wait a second... you guys aren't Orcs!'
'Show them how you'll kill those wretched Elf Archers!'
The Orc eyes you suspiciously...
'Anyways...'
'Very well...'
'Intruders!'
'Sir! How are you today sir?'
'Sound the alarm!'
'Sir! I am here to serve you sir!'
'To arms!'
'Sir! No sign of the intruders sir!'
'This armour's too heavy! It's time to show you my true strength!'
'Sir! You're looking... hmm...'
Once Commander Greb is killed, you can use this chest.
'Sir, do you have clearance to be here?'
'Sir, there are intruders in the stronghold! You must be... careful...'
'All right! Lunch time is over! Get back to work!'
You fail to disable the alarm and your cover has been blown!
'Sir... you look strange...'
'#-1:[placeholder] What's that smell? Smells like #-1:{an[E]|a} [placeholder]...'
'Sir! Permission to inspect you sir!'
'This armour hampers my reflexes!'
'Hmmm...'
As the Moria Sentry falls he lets forth a terrible wail that echoes throughout the halls.
'Sir... are you sure you're supposed to be here?'
'Do to them what you shall do to the trees of Lórien!'
'Who are you?'
'Now you shall witness my defences...'
The Moria Sentry lets out a blood curdling wail which shakes the very floor. Urgent voices echo through the halls.
The Sentry has activated the alarm!
The Moria Sentry cries even louder than the first as he falls. Hopefully his cries have fallen upon deaf ears.
'Who goes there?'
'You shall not pass!'
'Bah! My blades have lost their edge!'
'You fools are stronger than you look!'
'Let me see your papers...'
'Fools! I'll have to handle this myself...'
'We have intruders in our stronghold.'
'Are you new here?'
'If you can't stand the heat, get out of my kitchen!'
'Now I will school you in the ways of the warrior!'
'They may be disguised as Chief Guards. Don't let any pass.'
'Are you sure you're supposed to be here?'
'No more games! Prepare to fall to my flaming axe!'
'Get them!!!'
Once General Talug is killed, you can use this chest.
Once Vrarz the Cook is killed, you can use this chest.
The mess hall is filled with ravenous Orcs devouring their meals. Only an Orc would dare set foot in here...
'Only Commander Greb has clearance to pass here!'
You successfully disable the alarm and your cover is still intact.
'Ha! I don't know how you've made it this far, but your journey ends here!'
'Bar the doors! Let none of them escape!'
'Yes sir!'
'Fools! Don't just stand there! Help me!!'
You fail to disable the alarm, but your cover is still intact.
'Intruders! Intruders in the mess hall!'
'Who dares interrupt our meal? Get them!'
'Hey! A fresh meal has walked right to us boys!'
'Wait! Come back! There are intruders in our midsts!'
'Who dares interrupt me?'
The Orc stops staring at you.
